    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-01-22T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-01-22T14:00:00-05:00" n="784"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d784">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 300.115/6714</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-01-22T14:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 22, 1916, 2 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2765. Your 3606, January 20. Hops and lupulin are for use in brewing industries
                    and not for Government and are of kind not produced in United States or
                    procurable except from Germany or Austria. Desired that specific applications
                    for specific amounts may be made to British Embassy for permits for shipments.
                    Quantities to be limited in any event to normal consumption in United States of
                    German and Austrian hops. Proof to be furnished to <pb facs="0869" n="583"
                        xml:id="pg_583"/> British Embassy with each application that kind of hops or
                    lupulin desired by applicant can not be obtained elsewhere than in Germany or
                    Austria. Documents in case of one importer, <persName>Otto
                    Seidenberg</persName>, forwarded in Department’s instruction 3109 January
                        18.<note n="1" xml:id="d784fn1">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
